Football maverick Lionel Messi was presented with his sixth golden boot award on Wednesday, flanked by his two sons, Thiago and Mateo, as the Spanish football fraternity gathered to celebrate yet another remarkable year of brilliance from the Argentine international. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1272954 size-full" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=640%2C358&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="358" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=768%2C430&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=58%2C32&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/dc-Cover-mmlmijf9m7d6a7i3r6mb6ic0o1-20190525113418.Medi_.jpeg?resize=560%2C314&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> “Although we discuss the Champions League a lot, we never forget the league or cup at Barcelona,” Messi admitted. “The Champions League is something special, obviously, but the league is the most important thing, it’s what makes you feel good in the later rounds of the Champions League and the cup. “At Barcelona, we always aim to win everything.” As his two children took center stage at the award ceremony, Messi was quizzed on his role back at home, and the Argentine was quick to make clear he wasn’t in charge. “I better leave you with some doubt, generally the soft one is me,” Messi admitted. “The one who challenges the kids the most is above me. “Sometimes they deserve telling off, many times they deserve it.” With regards to the Golden Shoe award, the veteran forward was quick to thank those who have helped him along his journey. “Thank you all for being here to all those present, especially my family,” he added. “Luis and Jordi are here today, two big helps for me to receive this award. “Without my teammates, I wouldn’t have been able to receive even one of these, it’s a recognition of the entire team.” Source: Marca Vanguard News Virgil Van Dijk threatens to eclipse fellow European stars Cristiano Ronaldo and Lionel Messi to lift FIFA's The Best Player award on Monday, to set himself up as favourite for this year's Ballon d'Or. September 22, 2019 In "News" Lionel Messi collected a record fifth Golden Shoe award on Tuesday for finishing last season as the top goal scorer in Europe. December 18, 2018 In "News" Barcelona's Uruguayan star Luis Suarez on Thursday collected the Golden Shoe award for the leading scorer in Europe last season and admitted he never imagined being the most prolific member of such a star-studded attack. October 20, 2016 In "Sports"